events.name: Golden State Warriors at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 23 points with four 3-pointers in his annual homecoming game and the Golden State Warriors beat the Charlotte Hornets 115-97 on Friday night for their third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry returns home, scores 23 points to lead Warriors past Hornets 115-97

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Coach Rick Carlisle believes his Indiana Pacers are already in playoff mode.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pascal Siakam, Tyrese Haliburton combine for 43 points to lead Pacers past Lakers 109-90

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard and Paul George hit decisive jump shots in the final seconds for the Los Angeles Clippers, the Orlando Magic did not, and LA won for the fifth time in six road games, 100-97 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kawhi Leonard scores 29 to lead Clippers past Magic 100-97

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham scored 33 points, Jalen Duren had 20 points and 18 rebounds and the Detroit Pistons snapped an eight-game losing streak with a 96-87 victory over the Washington Wizards on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons snap 8-game skid, beating the Wizards 96-87 in a matchup of the NBA's bottom 2 teams

headlines.description: — Dennis Schroder and Mikal Bridges each made seven 3-pointers, and the Brooklyn Nets tied an NBA record by making 18 3s in the second half of their 125-108 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets tie NBA record with 18 3-pointers in a half, beat Bulls 125-108

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell looked different wearing a protective mask. With the All-Star guard finally back, so did the Cavaliers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell returns from injury, Mobley hits late 3-pointers as Cavaliers edge 76ers 117-114

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo had 21 points, 11 rebounds and nine assists and the Miami Heat had the largest margin of victory in team history, routing the Portland Trail Blazers 142-82 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat rout Trail Blazers 142-82 for largest margin of victory in team history

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Oklahoma City's No. 4 scorer has been playing more like a first option lately.
headlines.shortLinkText: Josh Giddey scores 23 points, Thunder rout Suns 128-103 without Gilgeous-Alexander

events.name: New York Knicks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama had a career-high 40 points and added 20 rebounds and seven assists, and the San Antonio Spurs overcame Jalen Brunson’s career-best 61 points to beat the New York Knicks 130-126 in overtime on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama has 40 points, 20 rebounds, Spurs overcome Brunson's 61 points to edge Knicks in OT

headlines.description: — This is why Glen Taylor doesn't want to let go of the Minnesota Timberwolves.
headlines.shortLinkText: Conley, Edwards lead surging Timberwolves past Nuggets 111-98 and into 1st-place tie in West

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 30 of his 34 points in the second half and had nine rebounds as the Houston Rockets beat the Utah Jazz 101-100 on Friday night for their 11th straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green scores 34, leads Rockets to 11th straight win with 101-100 victory over Jazz

headlines.description: — Dante Exum hit the winning 3-pointer with 27.5 seconds to go, Kyrie Irving had 30 points and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Sacramento Kings 107-103 on Friday night for their sixth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dante Exum hits late 3-pointer, Kyrie Irving scores 30 in Mavericks' 107-103 win over Kings
